author: Erica Dominguez
title: Watch Doug the Pug parody Fall Out Boy music videos in 'Irresistible'
text:
Play Fall Out Boy - "Irresistible" YouTube Earlier this week, Fall Out Boy announced they will be hitting the road once again in 2016. Along with confirming the tour announcement, the band also revealed that they had worked on a new version of their latest single, "Irresistible." On Friday morning (Oct. 16), the Chicago band kept their promise to fans and released the audio for the song which features vocals by pop star Demi Lovato .
Photo by Kevin Winter/Getty Images for iHeartMedia Throughout the song, frontman Patrick Stump and Lovato take turns singing parts of the song while also coming together for duets during the chorus and selected verses. For those liking the newly remade version of the track, it is currently available for purchase on iTunes and other digital media marketplaces.
In addition to the audio, the band also released a music video for the track featuring internet sensation, Doug the Pug. During the video, Doug the Pug is seen recreating several of Fall Out Boy's music videos including "Sugar, We're Going Down," "Dance, Dance," "Centuries," and even "Irresistible." Watch the music video for the song above.
Fall Out Boy is currently in the middle of their European tour. After a well-deserved break, the band will once again hit the road in early 2016. The tour, which will feature support from AWOLNATION and PVRIS, will officially kick off on Feb. 26 at the Seminole Hard Rock Live Arena in Hollywood, FL and wrap up a month later on March 26 at the Irvine Meadows Amphitheatre in Irvine, CA. Before their show in Florida, Fall Out Boy will perform at the Coliseo de Puerto Rico in San Juan, PR.
The complete itinerary for the "Wintour" can be seen here while general ticket sales are now available. Fall Out Boy released their latest album, American Beauty/ American Psycho back in January.
